<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,566,1866,1892]" box="[151,566,1866,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,566,1866,1892]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,566,1866,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[207,390,1866,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,390,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Delia coarctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1941,2007]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
In this species group, which equals the ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[633,817,1941,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis box="[633,817,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Delia coarctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superspecies’ of 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffiths" box="[1027,1216,1941,1967]" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1991) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 8, 1049 - 1240. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1991">
Griffiths (
<number box="[1144,1207,1941,1967]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, belong four presently accepted species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen" authorityName="Fallen" box="[437,693,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis box="[437,587,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D. coarctata</emphasis>
(Fallén)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Malloch" authorityName="Malloch" box="[709,981,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[709,851,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D. montana</emphasis>
(Malloch)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fan, Ma &amp; Li" authorityName="Fan, Ma &amp; Li" box="[997,1343,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis box="[997,1141,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D. latissima</emphasis>
(Fan, Ma &amp; Li)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1407,1436,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1435,152,338]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName box="[151,287,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctoides" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[151,287,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">coarctoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[303,448,152,178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. I agree with Griffiths (op. cit.) that the monophyly of the group appears well supported by the characteristic shape of the long surstyli that in caudal view are broad at base but turn very slen­ der distally (
<figureCitation box="[298,412,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1239,1263]" captionTargetBox="[292,1297,189,1181]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[260,1326,175,1219]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Hypopygium, caudal. 3. Delia coarctoides sp. nov. 4. D. coarctata (Fallén). Notice shape of cercal plate. Same scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175667/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Figs. 
<number box="[364,412,232,258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1435,152,338]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
The following practical key to the males and females of the 
<taxonomicName box="[901,1084,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis box="[901,1084,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Delia coarctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group uses characters that are normally visible without dissection.
</paragraph>
